data.meta_site_name: Alana Stoehr Obituary | April 7, 2024 | Verkuilen Funeral Home - Kaukauna, WI
data.text:
Alana E. Stoehr, age 22, passed away unexpectedly on April 7, 2024. She was born on August 9, 2001 and attended Kimberly Schools. Alana was a free spirit, strong willed, funny and had a passion for music. She enjoyed spending time with her family at their cottage on Legend Lake. She was a beautiful soul and will be deeply missed.

Alana is survived by her parents, Dean and Jennifer (Pierre) Stoehr; little brother, Mason Stoehr; grandparents: Karen Stoehr, Dan and Gale Pierre; uncles: David Stoehr, Jason (Erin) Pierre and Andy Pierre; cousins: Bella and Weston Pierre; dog Zoey and many extended family and friends.

Alana was preceded in death by her grandfathers: Bill Brunette and Donald Stoehr; great-grandmothers: Hazel Smits and Katherine Casper.

A memorial gathering will take place for Alana on Thursday, April 11, 2024, from 4:00 p.m. until 6:00 p.m. at the Verkuilen-Van Deurzen Family Funeral Home Kaukauna Location, 2401 Fieldcrest Drive. Interment will take place at St. Paul Cemetery, Combined Locks. For online condolences, please visit www.verkuilenfh.com.
